info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Shifts the values inside a measure array by 'offset' positions using the 'filling' value.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_long';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
					'oph_double';
					'oph_float';
					'oph_int';
					'oph_short';
					'oph_byte'.
- measure : input measure.
- offset : number of movements of 1 measure.
           If >0, the shift will be to the right.
           If <0, the shift will be to the left.
           With 0, there will be no shift.
- filling : number used to fill empty elements during the shift.

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Shifts to the left the values inside a measure array by 2 positions using 0 as filling value.
oph_shift('OPH_DOUBLE','OPH_DOUBLE',measure,-2,0)
